 Sanbao, 5 years old, lives near the Shaolin Temple in the Songshan Mountain, Central China's Henan Provinc. He started learning Kungfu two years and a half ago. Sanbao's teacher, Shi Yandian, a 34th-generation disciple of Shaolin Temple, is an inheritor of Shaolin Kungfu, a national intangible cultural heritage. Both Sanbao and his teacher now have millions of fans on China's social media. Sanbao has become very popular now and in Octoberof this year he was invited to give performance at Jackie Chan International Action Movie Festival. Watch the video to see Sanbao's daily life practising Kungfu. Video credit to "Shaolin Temple Shi Yandian" (kuaishou#501352197), posted on Chinese online video-sharing platform Kuaishou, as well as "Shaolin Sanbao", posted on Chinese online video-sharing platform Douyin (the Chinese version of TikTok). (Source: Kuaishou & Douyin) 